s of 56Ni mixing, and/or larger progenitor radii than slowly\nfading Type II supernovae, so that the light-curve bump does not become\nsignificant.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Oct 2015 16:44:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-12"}
