nd accuracy (0.07), outperforming the other two\napproaches. Drawing random points from the light curve gives rise to typically\n57% of outliers and an accuracy of 0.4. Adding GALEX/IRAC bands for the\nredshift determination weakens the influence of variability. Although the\nredshift quality generally improves when adding these bands, we still obtain\nnot less than 26% of outliers and an accuracy of 0.05 at best, therefore\nvariable sources should receive a flag stating that their photo-z may be low\nquality.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Oct 2015 20:04:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-02"}
